Marks & Spencer Hires Morrison’s Taylor as Simply Food Director

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-04-07T18:58:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/marks-spencer-hires-morrison-s-taylor-as-simply-food-director.html
Marks & Spencer Group Plc (MKS)  hired
Christopher Taylor, a senior manager at  WM Morrison Supermarkets
Plc (MRW) , as director of Simply Food, franchise and hospitality,
replacing Neil Hyslop, who becomes director of space planning
and development, Marks & Spencer spokesman Philip Sorensen said
by telephone today.  Taylor was responsible for developing Morrison’s new
convenience store program, Morrison spokesman Julian Bailey said
by telephone today. The convenience store program will now be
overseen by Miles Foster, Bailey said.  Morrison’s convenience store program is “on track” and
will open its first store in July, Bailey also said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 